title: 40. The Suicide Paradox
description: There are more than twice as many suicides as murders in the U.S., but suicide attracts far less scrutiny. Freakonomics Radio digs through the numbers and finds all kinds of surprises.
author: editor@freakonomics.com (Freakonomics Radio + Stitcher)
